01:29:12.090 --> 01:29:16.270
Chief Allston, you used a
term that may be unfamiliar

01:29:16.270 --> 01:29:20.250
to many folk, and that
term is paper genocide.

01:29:20.250 --> 01:29:24.510
Would you please explain
what paper genocide means?

01:29:24.510 --> 01:29:29.680
&gt;&gt; Lynette Lewis Allston: Well,
over time, identity is lost.

01:29:29.680 --> 01:29:34.950
Within our tribe, we find people
on census records and early

01:29:34.950 --> 01:29:38.450
on listed IND, Indian.

01:29:38.450 --> 01:29:45.330
But over time, that IND
changed to mulatto, MU.

01:29:45.330 --> 01:29:48.350
Or in some instances,
it was changed to white.

01:29:48.350 --> 01:29:52.730
And in other instances,
it was changed to black.

01:29:52.730 --> 01:29:58.350
And then we go to the
point that it's either a W

01:29:58.350 --> 01:30:04.020
or a C. You've effectively
erased an entire culture just

01:30:04.020 --> 01:30:08.800
by changing the markings
on a piece of paper.

01:30:08.800 --> 01:30:13.120
The census takers who came to
visit would look at someone

01:30:13.120 --> 01:30:16.500
and just say oh, I think this
is what this person looks like,

01:30:16.500 --> 01:30:19.080
and that's what I'm
going to call them.

01:30:19.080 --> 01:30:23.100
And so, identity was lost.

01:30:23.100 --> 01:30:28.730
I referred to the 1924
Racial Integrity Act,

01:30:28.730 --> 01:30:35.370
which was the final blow
on negative culture.

01:30:35.370 --> 01:30:36.890
Interesting enough,
there's something

01:30:36.890 --> 01:30:41.000
in there called the Pocahontas
exception, which if you happen

01:30:41.000 --> 01:30:45.810
to be a certain percentage
of Indian,

01:30:45.810 --> 01:30:51.200
you could still claim
your European heritage.

01:30:51.200 --> 01:30:57.050
But it was because you
connected back to Pocahontas.

01:30:57.050 --> 01:31:01.600
So that's also part of
this identity issue.

01:31:01.600 --> 01:31:06.130
But that is also something that
affects our Native population

01:31:06.130 --> 01:31:10.280
because we are afraid to
admit we have some segments

01:31:10.280 --> 01:31:15.930
of our native community, are
afraid to admit that we are made

01:31:15.930 --> 01:31:21.670
up of multiple ethnic
or racial background.

01:31:21.670 --> 01:31:26.900
And paper genocide led us down
that road, and we are happy now

01:31:26.900 --> 01:31:31.020
that we're able to
reverse that cycle.

