01:38:32.910 --> 01:38:36.770
in terms of how to cover it
why you're using that phrase.

01:38:36.770 --> 01:38:39.940
&gt;&gt; Joanne Braxton: This
folk were not born slaves.

01:38:39.940 --> 01:38:43.930
They had to be made into slaves.

01:38:43.930 --> 01:38:46.750
There are these places
along the coast,

01:38:46.750 --> 01:38:50.510
especially in West Africa, and
I've seen quite a few of them.

01:38:50.510 --> 01:38:53.640
And if you'd like to visit
them without going there,

01:38:53.640 --> 01:38:56.700
you can go to the Middle
Passage Project page

01:38:56.700 --> 01:38:59.540
on William &amp; Mary
dot edu website,

01:38:59.540 --> 01:39:05.400
and you can see Elmina
and Cape Coast.

01:39:05.400 --> 01:39:13.310
Some of these folks were marched
mercilessly from the interior.

01:39:13.310 --> 01:39:17.050
Maybe a third of the people
who started out on the journey

01:39:17.050 --> 01:39:20.150
to the sea didn't make it.

01:39:20.150 --> 01:39:23.200
Some would be yoked together.

01:39:23.200 --> 01:39:26.260
People would be yoked
in cockles.

01:39:26.260 --> 01:39:29.220
People whose health was not good

01:39:29.220 --> 01:39:34.320
or was failing might be
left in the bush to die.

01:39:34.320 --> 01:39:37.950
Small children might be
considered liabilities.

01:39:37.950 --> 01:39:42.950
They might be left
in the bush to die.

01:39:42.950 --> 01:39:46.850
But a day before, they may
simply have been taking a walk

01:39:46.850 --> 01:39:48.570
in the woods.

01:39:48.570 --> 01:39:50.140
You could have been
taking a walk

01:39:50.140 --> 01:39:54.800
in the woods somewhere near
what is present day Accra today

01:39:54.800 --> 01:40:01.150
with a loved one, and one of
you could be taken to Elmina.

01:40:01.150 --> 01:40:04.510
One of you could be
taken to Cape Coast.

01:40:04.510 --> 01:40:07.630
One of you would go to
a Portuguese territory.

01:40:07.630 --> 01:40:09.910
One of you would go to
an English territory.

01:40:09.910 --> 01:40:13.610
And you have a first cousin

01:40:13.610 --> 01:40:17.010
in Brazil while you're
in Jamestown.

01:40:17.010 --> 01:40:22.370
So, so many times the
faces seem similar.

01:40:22.370 --> 01:40:26.490
And when those people
left through those doors

01:40:26.490 --> 01:40:32.890
of no return, some of which
were about 15 inches wide,

01:40:32.890 --> 01:40:39.260
too narrow for you to go through
forward, just straight forward.

01:40:39.260 --> 01:40:42.240
They would have to march
side-by-side to be able

01:40:42.240 --> 01:40:43.680
to go through the door.

01:40:43.680 --> 01:40:48.000
And most frequently, they
were taken out at night

01:40:48.000 --> 01:40:55.310
because when they
would see the coast

01:40:55.310 --> 01:41:01.730
of their nation falling away in
the distance in the daylight,

01:41:01.730 --> 01:41:04.120
some of them would
just stop breathing.

01:41:04.120 --> 01:41:09.570
And they refused to
be made into slaves.

01:41:09.570 --> 01:41:13.930
And if you would
go to Elmina, also,

01:41:13.930 --> 01:41:16.310
you would see there's a door.

01:41:16.310 --> 01:41:22.000
There are two doors actually.

01:41:22.000 --> 01:41:28.740
If you were to stand in the
Dutch reform chapel in Elmina,

01:41:28.740 --> 01:41:32.190
which is directly over
the women's dungeon,

01:41:32.190 --> 01:41:34.280
and you would look out,
you would see two doors.

01:41:34.280 --> 01:41:36.240
They were for punishment.

01:41:36.240 --> 01:41:38.170
One was for Europeans

01:41:38.170 --> 01:41:42.730
who infringed upon some
crime while they were there.

01:41:42.730 --> 01:41:44.770
And the others were for
Africans who refused

01:41:44.770 --> 01:41:47.150
to be made into slaves.

01:41:47.150 --> 01:41:50.660
Over that a door there is
a skull and crossbones.

01:41:50.660 --> 01:41:57.570
And they would put as many as
four or five people int hat room

01:41:57.570 --> 01:42:02.490
at a time, these Africans who
refused to be made into slaves.

01:42:02.490 --> 01:42:06.700
And no one came out of
that door until everyone

01:42:06.700 --> 01:42:09.470
in that room was dead.

01:42:09.470 --> 01:42:12.880
You don't have to
believe my story.

01:42:12.880 --> 01:42:14.940
You can check it out.

01:42:14.940 --> 01:42:19.180
It is so utterly
and shockingly true.

01:42:19.180 --> 01:42:24.050
And the photographs of those
locations are available

01:42:24.050 --> 01:42:26.350
to you for viewing.

01:42:31.380 --> 01:42:36.100
So, it's to acknowledge
the humanity of individuals

01:42:36.100 --> 01:42:42.830
as human beings, with,
we would presume,

01:42:42.830 --> 01:42:45.960
inalienably human rights.

