of what happens to
the person's body.

01:44:26.810 --> 01:44:31.420
It's a question of what
happens to their spirit.

01:44:31.420 --> 01:44:36.290
And we have to think really
about the young people

01:44:36.290 --> 01:44:41.980
who survive physically these
traumatic events but walk away

01:44:41.980 --> 01:44:47.340
with invisible wounds that
are not unlike the wounds

01:44:47.340 --> 01:44:51.960
that someone would
sustain on a battlefield.

01:44:51.960 --> 01:44:55.040
The walking wounded.

01:44:55.040 --> 01:44:57.330
Is that making sense?

01:44:57.330 --> 01:45:02.330
But you will be able
to find more precise

01:45:02.330 --> 01:45:06.530
and abundant references by
consulting her directly.

01:45:11.040 --> 01:45:13.680
And the other panelists are
available to field questions

01:45:13.680 --> 01:45:17.350
as well, so feel free to
direct questions toward them.

01:45:17.350 --> 01:45:19.630
&gt;&gt; Hi, my name is Jama Kelvey
